---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Seychelles Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/seychelles/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Mauritius for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/mauritius' },
  { title: 'Maldives for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/maldives' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'seychellesFit', header: 'Seychelles Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'SCR 6,000-8,500/mo', seychellesFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'SCR 7,000-10,000/mo', seychellesFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'SCR 5,500-7,900/mo', seychellesFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'SCR 5,000-7,200/mo', seychellesFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Seychelles Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'SCR 1,500-4,000/mo', seychellesFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'SCR 5,500-8,500', annual: 'SCR 66,000-102,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'SCR 7,500-11,500', annual: 'SCR 90,000-138,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'SCR 10,000-15,500', annual: 'SCR 120,000-186,000' },
  { category: 'Seychelles Public Hospital', monthly: 'Free for residents', annual: 'Limited services' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'SCR 500-1,500/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Seychelles 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Seychelles. Paradise islands, limited healthcare, evacuation essential, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Seychelles"
  subheadline="Seychelles offers paradise islands, pristine beaches, and unique wildlife—but limited healthcare means evacuation coverage is essential for senior retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/seychelles-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Seychelles</h2>
  <p>
    Seychelles offers paradise—115 islands with pristine beaches, unique wildlife (giant tortoises), and Creole culture. English is official, making communication easy. The lifestyle is relaxed and nature-focused. For wealthy retirees seeking exclusive island living, Seychelles delivers.
  </p>

  <p>
    Mahe is the main island with capital Victoria and best services. Praslin offers quieter island life. La Digue is car-free paradise. The archipelago is small—everything is accessible but costs are high and healthcare limited.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; evacuation essential</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English, French, Creole</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> SCR 35,000-80,000/month (~$2,500-5,800); very high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Paradise islands; exclusive; nature-focused</li>
      <li><strong>Investment:</strong> High threshold for residence</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Seychelles Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Seychelles healthcare is limited—small island nation with basic facilities. Seychelles Hospital on Mahe handles routine care. For anything complex, evacuation to South Africa, India, or Dubai is necessary. This is the key consideration for senior retirees.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is free for residents but basic. Private options are limited. International insurance with comprehensive evacuation coverage is essential—not optional—for senior health security in Seychelles.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Evacuation Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Seychelles is a small island nation (97,000 population) with limited medical capabilities. Complex conditions, serious emergencies, and most surgeries require evacuation. South Africa (4+ hours), Dubai, or India are typical destinations. International insurance with evacuation coverage is mandatory for seniors.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Seychelles has high barriers for long-term residence:
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Permit</h3>
  <p>
    Significant investment required—typically $1 million+ in approved business or real estate. Provides residence permit. High threshold but straightforward for qualified investors.
  </p>

  <h3>Gainful Occupation Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For those with employment or business. Not a retirement visa but some retirees structure businesses to qualify.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Visa-free entry for most nationalities up to 3 months. Extensions possible. Some retirees use extended visits while pursuing formal residence.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Seychelles:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence permit:</strong> Health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Essential given limited local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage level:</strong> Comprehensive international coverage needed</li>
    <li><strong>Destinations:</strong> South Africa, India, Dubai for evacuation</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Seychelles</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with comprehensive evacuation is essential—not optional. Local healthcare handles minor issues only. Plan must cover air ambulance to South Africa, India, or Dubai. This is the most critical consideration for Seychelles retirement.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Seychelles, evacuation coverage is the priority:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Seychelles</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong evacuation network, Indian Ocean coverage</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Regional expertise, good evacuation protocols</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Global evacuation network</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with evacuation essential for Seychelles islands.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Seychelles are high given evacuation requirements:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Do not skimp:</strong> Evacuation coverage is essential—not the place to cut costs</li>
    <li><strong>High deductibles:</strong> Can work for routine care; keep evacuation comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Indian Ocean + evacuation destinations</li>
    <li><strong>Routine care cash:</strong> Minor local consultations can be cash payment</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Wealthy British Investor, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £1.5M property investment. £4,000/month passive income.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Investor permit. Cigna Global comprehensive with UK and SA evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~SCR 7,500/month (~£450). Paradise lifestyle with full health security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: South African Couple, Both 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Business investment. Combined income ZAR 80,000/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. SA evacuation easily accessible (4 hours).</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~SCR 18,000/month combined (~ZAR 20,000). Island paradise; home country healthcare backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: French Entrepreneur, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Hotel business investment. €5,000/month income.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Business permit. Allianz with France evacuation option.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Allianz ~SCR 6,500/month (~€450). Creole culture; French connections.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How limited is Seychelles healthcare really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very limited. Basic care is available—minor injuries, common illnesses, basic surgery. Anything complex (cardiac, oncology, major surgery) requires evacuation. Small population (97,000) cannot support specialized services. Plan for evacuation as standard.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Seychelles expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very expensive—island nation importing most goods. Groceries 2-3x European prices. Property is expensive. Budget $3,000-6,000/month minimum for comfortable retirement. This is a destination for wealthy retirees, not budget seekers.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the investment threshold?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        High—typically $1 million+ for residence through investment. Seychelles is selective about residents. This limits retirement to high-net-worth individuals. Not a destination for average pension income.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Seychelles suitable for seniors with health conditions?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Challenging—limited local care means frequent evacuation may be needed for chronic conditions. Healthy, active seniors fare better. Those with complex health needs should consider destinations with better local healthcare. Honest assessment of health status is essential.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes with comprehensive evacuation coverage for Seychelles.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Seychelles authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
